At the start of the year, I booked a one way ticket to Paris with the dream of living in Europe for some time. 

That ticket was three years in the making. Dreams are so easily conjured but rarely manifested. From three years until a week before my departure date, I was still unsure if I would fly. 

Three weeks in and every struggle now seems worth it.

Many people asked me why I'm going back to Paris again. 
Why? Because Paris doesn't exist. There are as many versions of Paris as there are inhabitants. Each person has a different experience of it, a different network of places and references, an everchanging ensemble that is representative of the city as they see it.
I found the answer in the foreward of a book, Ma Vie A Paris, in a small bookstore by the Seine.

Grateful to these beautiful humans for an unforgettable start to my birthday celebrations. Your presence and love means the world to me ♥️ Cheers to making more memories we can marinate over 🍾🍾 @pdas5 @rellicdragon_ @arpitaab @riditatheexplorer @anibiswaaas @roe_moz @overtheordinary

This year had some incredible highs and challenging lows. One of my greatest achievements this year was a 2 month Euro trip that Apple has labeled as “world tour” - & attending my first-ever Formula 1 race. Grateful for the incredible highs, getting through lowest of the lows, and ending the year with positivity & love.
